Add an optional `_streaming` boolean to the `ChatMessage` interface and tag all messages created during streaming with `_streaming: true`. This flag marks messages that have client-generated UUIDs awaiting server ID reconciliation.

## Files to Modify

### 1. `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/chat-types.ts`

Add `_streaming?: boolean` to the `ChatMessage` interface (after `commandArgs`):

```typescript
export interface ChatMessage {
  id: string;
  role: 'user' | 'assistant';
  content: string;
  toolCalls?: ToolCallState[];
  parts: MessagePart[];
  timestamp: string;
  messageType?: 'command' | 'compaction';
  commandName?: string;
  commandArgs?: string;
  /** @internal Client-only tag for streaming messages awaiting server ID reconciliation. */
  _streaming?: boolean;
}
```

This follows the existing underscore-prefix convention for client-only fields (`_partId` in `StreamingTextPart` at `stream-event-types.ts:9-12`).

### 2. `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/use-chat-session.ts`

In `executeSubmission`, add `_streaming: true` to the optimistic user message (around line 391-400):

```typescript
setMessages((prev) => [
  ...prev,
  {
    id: pendingUserId,
    role: 'user' as const,
    content,
    parts: [{ type: 'text', text: content }],
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
    _streaming: true,
  },
]);
```

### 3. `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/stream-event-helpers.ts`

In `ensureAssistantMessage` (around line 71-86), add `_streaming: true` to the assistant message:

```typescript
function ensureAssistantMessage(assistantId: string) {
  if (!assistantCreatedRef.current) {
    assistantCreatedRef.current = true;
    setMessages((prev) => [
      ...prev,
      {
        id: assistantId,
        role: 'assistant',
        content: '',
        toolCalls: [],
        parts: [],
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
        _streaming: true,
      },
    ]);
  }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `ChatMessage` interface has `_streaming?: boolean` field with TSDoc `@internal` annotation
- [ ] Optimistic user message in `executeSubmission` has `_streaming: true`
- [ ] Assistant message in `ensureAssistantMessage` has `_streaming: true`
- [ ] TypeScript compiles without errors (`pnpm typecheck`)
- [ ] Existing tests pass (`pnpm vitest run apps/client`)

Remove the post-stream `historySeededRef.current = false` reset and `queryClient.invalidateQueries` call that causes the message flash bug. After streaming ends, local messages stay as-is. The existing polling interval (`refetchInterval` on the history query) handles eventual consistency.

## Files to Modify

### `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/use-chat-session.ts`

In `executeSubmission`, replace the post-stream reset block (lines 431-440) with just the cleanup:

**Before** (lines 431-440):
```typescript
// Reset seed flag so the next history fetch does a full replace instead of
// an incremental append. This prevents ID-mismatch duplicates: the streaming
// assistant has a client-generated UUID while history has an SDK-assigned UUID.
historySeededRef.current = false;
pendingUserIdRef.current = null;
// Invalidate broadly to cover session ID remaps (client UUID → SDK UUID).
// The old targetSessionId may differ from the SDK-assigned ID returned in
// the done event, so a narrow key would miss the active query.
queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['messages'] });
setStatus('idle');
```

**After:**
```typescript
pendingUserIdRef.current = null;
setStatus('idle');
```

Remove the three deleted lines:
1. `historySeededRef.current = false;` — was causing the seed effect to use Branch 1 (full replace) instead of Branch 2 (incremental append), which triggers the flash
2. `queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['messages'] });` — was forcing an immediate refetch that arrived with stale data, causing the flash. The existing `refetchInterval` on the history query handles eventual consistency.
3. Keep `pendingUserIdRef.current = null;` and `setStatus('idle');`

## Why This Is Safe

- The seed effect's Branch 2 (incremental append at lines 299-306) handles new messages arriving via polling
- Tagged-dedup (task 1.3) handles the ID mismatch between client UUIDs and server UUIDs
- The polling interval ensures messages eventually converge with the server state
- Removing the invalidation eliminates one extra network request per streaming completion

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `historySeededRef.current = false` removed from the try block in `executeSubmission`
- [ ] `queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['messages'] })` removed
- [ ] `pendingUserIdRef.current = null` and `setStatus('idle')` remain
- [ ] Manual test: send a message, observe no flash when agent finishes responding
- [ ] Existing tests pass (`pnpm vitest run apps/client`)

Rewrite the seed effect's Branch 2 (incremental append path) to handle tagged streaming messages. When server history arrives via polling, match tagged messages by content (user) or position (assistant), carry over client-only parts, and clear the `_streaming` flag.

## Files to Modify

### `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/use-chat-session.ts`

Replace the current Branch 2 logic (lines 299-306):

**Before:**
```typescript
if (historySeededRef.current && !isStreaming) {
  const currentIds = new Set(messagesRef.current.map((m) => m.id));
  const newMessages = history.filter((m) => !currentIds.has(m.id));

  if (newMessages.length > 0) {
    setMessages((prev) => [...prev, ...newMessages.map(mapHistoryMessage)]);
  }
}
```

**After:**
```typescript
if (historySeededRef.current && !isStreaming) {
  const currentIds = new Set(messagesRef.current.map((m) => m.id));
  const taggedMessages = messagesRef.current.filter((m) => m._streaming);

  // Find the tagged user message (if any) for content matching
  const taggedUser = taggedMessages.find((m) => m.role === 'user');
  const taggedAssistant = taggedMessages.find((m) => m.role === 'assistant');

  const newMessages: typeof history = [];
  let matchedUserIdx = -1;

  for (let i = 0; i < history.length; i++) {
    const serverMsg = history[i];
    if (currentIds.has(serverMsg.id)) continue;

    // Try to match tagged user message by exact content
    if (
      taggedUser &&
      serverMsg.role === 'user' &&
      serverMsg.content === taggedUser.content
    ) {
      matchedUserIdx = i;
      // Replace tagged user with server version, clear tag
      setMessages((prev) =>
        prev.map((m) =>
          m.id === taggedUser.id
            ? { ...mapHistoryMessage(serverMsg), _streaming: false }
            : m,
        ),
      );
      continue;
    }

    // Match tagged assistant by position (immediately after matched user)
    if (
      taggedAssistant &&
      matchedUserIdx >= 0 &&
      i === matchedUserIdx + 1 &&
      serverMsg.role === 'assistant'
    ) {
      // Carry over client-only parts that the server version lacks
      const serverMapped = mapHistoryMessage(serverMsg);
      const clientOnlyParts = taggedAssistant.parts.filter(
        (p) => p.type === 'error' || p.type === 'subagent' || p.type === 'hook',
      );
      const mergedParts =
        clientOnlyParts.length > 0
          ? [...serverMapped.parts, ...clientOnlyParts]
          : serverMapped.parts;

      setMessages((prev) =>
        prev.map((m) =>
          m.id === taggedAssistant.id
            ? { ...serverMapped, parts: mergedParts, _streaming: false }
            : m,
        ),
      );
      continue;
    }

    // No match — append as new message (existing behavior)
    newMessages.push(serverMsg);
  }

  if (newMessages.length > 0) {
    setMessages((prev) => [...prev, ...newMessages.map(mapHistoryMessage)]);
  }
}
```

## Key Properties

- Tagged set is bounded at 0-2 messages per streaming turn (one user, one assistant)
- Tags are cleared on match, so no unbounded growth
- User message matched by exact content (client submitted it, content is identical)
- Assistant message matched by position (immediately following the matched user in server history)
- Client-only parts (`error`, `subagent`, `hook`) are carried over to the server version since the transcript parser doesn't return them (until Phase 2 completes)
- Unmatched server messages are appended normally (preserves existing behavior for cross-client sync)

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Tagged user messages are matched by exact content and replaced with server version
- [ ] Tagged assistant messages are matched by position (after matched user) and replaced
- [ ] Client-only parts (error, subagent, hook) are carried over to merged message
- [ ] `_streaming` flag is cleared to `false` on match
- [ ] Unmatched server messages are still appended normally
- [ ] No duplicate messages appear in the UI
- [ ] TypeScript compiles without errors
- [ ] Unit tests written and passing (see test requirements below)

