Implement the `getLastMessageIds` method in `ClaudeCodeRuntime` that reads the JSONL transcript and returns the SDK-assigned IDs for the last user and assistant messages.

## Files to Modify

### `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/claude-code-runtime.ts`

Add the implementation. The method uses the existing `TranscriptReader` to get messages and walks backward to find the last user and assistant IDs:

```typescript
/** @inheritdoc */
async getLastMessageIds(
  sessionId: string,
): Promise<{ user: string; assistant: string } | null> {
  try {
    // Use the project dir from the session, falling back to DEFAULT_CWD
    const session = this.sessions.get(sessionId);
    const projectDir = session?.cwd ?? DEFAULT_CWD;
    const messages = await this.transcriptReader.getMessages(projectDir, sessionId);
    if (!messages?.length) return null;

    let lastUser: string | null = null;
    let lastAssistant: string | null = null;

    for (let i = messages.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
      const m = messages[i];
      if (!lastAssistant && m.role === 'assistant') lastAssistant = m.id;
      if (!lastUser && m.role === 'user') lastUser = m.id;
      if (lastUser && lastAssistant) break;
    }

    if (!lastUser || !lastAssistant) return null;
    return { user: lastUser, assistant: lastAssistant };
  } catch (err) {
    logger.warn('[getLastMessageIds] failed to read transcript', {
      sessionId,
      error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err),
    });
    return null;
  }
}
```

Note: The `TranscriptReader` is already injected into `ClaudeCodeRuntime` as `this.transcriptReader`. The `getMessages` method reads and parses the JSONL file. This method is called once after streaming completes, when the file is already in the OS page cache.

